title: Sweden faces Denmark in Euro 2016 playoffs derby
text:
Sweden faces Denmark in Euro 2016 playoffs derby Source: Shanghai Daily | October 19, 2015, Monday | Print Edition 
Zlatan Ibrahimovicâ€™s Sweden will face Denmark in a Nordic derby in the Euro 2016 playoffs. 
Norway, another Nordic nation chasing one of the remaining four spots at the expanded 24-team tournament, was drawn yesterday to play Hungary in the two-legged playoffs next month. Ireland, which qualified for Euro 2012 through the playoffs, faces Bosnia-Herzegovina this time. In a repeat of a Euro 2000 playoff, Ukraine and Slovenia were paired together again. Slovenia won back in 1999.
